Course_desc: This course explores the concepts, trends, and practices in psychological counseling, covering sub-topics such as its nature, foundations, psychological theories, the role of the counselor, and the various methods used in psychological counseling. Additionally, it aims to delineate the skills essential for psychological counseling and the factors that may influence it. Furthermore, the course seeks to establish connections between this field and other sciences
